*******************************************************************************
       Name: Dispel Object
       Kind: Spell
     Target: TAR_IGNORE
   Position: POS_FIGHTING
   Min Mana: 15
 Wait Beats: 12
 Can Learn: FALSE
Noun Damage: None
   Wear-Off: !Dispel Object!
Acquisition:
   - Magi: level 60
   - Cleric: level 70
   - Psionicist: level 80
Description:
   Dispel Object strips magical flags and all applied enchantments from a
   carried item. The spell targets an item in the caster's inventory (or
   passed via object targeting).

   Flags removed by Dispel Object:
     ITEM_EVIL      -- "X looks less evil."
     ITEM_NODROP    -- Silently removed (item becomes droppable again).
     ITEM_INVIS     -- "X fades back into view."
     ITEM_MAGIC     -- "X looks less magical."
     ITEM_BLESS     -- "X looks less Holy."
     ITEM_NOREMOVE  -- Silently removed (item becomes removable again).

   In addition to removing flags, ALL applied enchantments (first_apply /
   last_apply linked list) are wiped from the item. This is permanent and
   irreversible -- enchantments removed by Dispel Object cannot be
   re-applied without re-enchanting the item from scratch.

   Note: Because dispel object removes the apply list, it interacts with the
   enchant command: an item that has been dispelled can be re-enchanted
   normally, since the enchant system checks for existing enchantments before
   allowing a new enchantment to be applied.

   Primary use cases:
     - Removing a curse (ITEM_NODROP) from an item without using Remove Curse.
     - Stripping an invisible or evil-flagged item of its flags.
     - Clearing an item's enchantments before re-enchanting with new stats.
*******************************************************************************
